Main Entry: 1com·pro·mise <br>
Pronunciation: 'käm-pr&amp;-&quot;mIz<br>
Function: noun<br>
1 a : settlement of differences by arbitration or by consent reached by mutual concessions b : something intermediate between or blending qualities of two different things<br>
<br>
I'm using defintion (a) <br>
<br>
The above 'compromise' is not a compromise at all. It is a rationalization.  For it to be a compromise, both parties (those capable of killing solo, and those incapable of killing solo) would have to 'give' a little.<br>
<br>
For instance, a compromise would be:<br>
<br>
If you wish to team up to kill a pop flagging mob, you and your team become an RTA recognized alliance for (determine a fair and fitting time duration) month(s) for every pop flag mob you kill.<br>
<br>
Example:  Guild X, on 5 pre-pop rotations, Guild Y on 4 pre-pop rotations.  They merge to kill AD 2x, Behe 2x and Grummus 2x.<br>
<br>
The two guilds are now recognized as a single unity for 1 month (pretend that's the agreed penalty) per kill of a flag mob (in this case for 6 months they would be considered an alliance).<br>
<br>
Guild X and Y now merge together on thier 5 pre-pop rotations for 6 months, assuming they do not continue to team up on various flag encounters - they would then return back to two separate RTA recognized entities.<br>
<br>
This would be a compromise. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.drow.org/eq/roster/view.php?Emil" target="top">Emil Sinclair</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, 65th Monk<br>
