No, you adhere to the absolute letter of the law while completing bankrupting the spirit of it.  No one has teamed on THO, Sont, Vindi, etc all the examples of “no one would say anything IF”, they’re all hypotheticals.  Well wake up, because I’m talking about two dead Aerin Dars, not hypotheticals, and a complete 180 from the way things have been handled on our server for the last three years.  All because of flags for a zone that there is a quest for.  So go do the quest. . .and get your xp.<br>
<br>
Sprigg,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> 1) They are neccessary in a guilds capacity to progress through the game.<br>
2) No rotation is needed since this content is not contested.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The last time NB went to do the Chardok royals for new recruits and alts, the Royals were taken.  Same thing with the last time we went to do Aerin Dar.  How do you justify calling it uncontested?<br>
<br>
Let me paint a simple picture for you.  BOTS, NB, Tindi, VOF, SOTE, LoM, FK, ED, CB, VOLS all have members flagged for HoH.  I won’t bother listing the remaining guilds that are NOT flagged for HoH, but let’s settle on a number of 30+.  30+ guilds all after the same mob to get into HoH, and you call it uncontested?!?  By what measure?!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> The difference is that the content further down the line will probably be contested, especially as more guilds make it to that far.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Probably?  First, I don’t like probably, maybe or other words of doubt when it comes to something like this.  Second, to follow Korwynn’s or your advice on “hey, just let this one slide till we get to something you really care about”, is advocating being exactly what we are accused of: narrow self-interest.  It’s the principle of the thing that bothers me, not HoH the zone itself (trials being blown is another matter).  I agree with Gromm and others who have pointed out, that if this precedent is allowed, these same guilds or others that follow will cry foul and point to this example as why they are bein’ oppressed for not being allowed to team Rallos or Mith Marr or HoH trials.  After all, they couldn’t kill Aerin Dar alone, there is no way in hell they’ll be able to do Rydda Dar with less capability than they had for Aerin Dar.  Also, one gets xp during an HoH trial raid. . and there’s loot. . .<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roggulbuk>Roggulbuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><marquee>Newbie Admin!</marquee> <BR>
Watch him break stuff!</span><br>  Posts: 1292<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/16/03 1:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=646.topic&index=289>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Response to Teamwork thread in guild rep forum.</span><hr size=1> There are times when even mobs that are not on rotation, should not be teamed against, ever. My distinction has been, the entire time, that if there is a quest that allows you to pass the mob, than you should be able to team on the mob. <br>
<br>
THIS IS A BRAND NEW SITUATION (Caps for emphasis, not yelling)<br>
<br>
And as such, brand new rules can and should apply to it. It is also my contention, as a member of a guild that *cannot* kill most of the PoP flagging mobs, that small guilds should not be allowed to team on mobs that *cannot* be quested past. <br>
<br>
The zones beyond drop loot that is 'guarded' by the flagging encounter. Teaming on mobs that cannot be quested past, to me, is like teaming up to kill a rotation mob;<br>
<br>
a. The mob is obviously desired; the fact that it has been left up for days, or weeks, is not an issue to prove or disprove desire. Why would any guild try to kill the mob, let alone get together with another guild, if the mob was not desired. If the mob is desired, it has at least one of the qualities of a rotation mob. <br>
<br>
b. The mob has loot, or a benefit from killing it, that is very valuable. The ability to move to the next zone is very valuable, proven by the fact that two guilds or more would have the interest to come together to kill this one mob. When's the last time two guilds got together to raid in crushbone? The benefit from killing it provides the second quality of a rotation mob.<br>
<br>
c. The mob has a suitably long respawn time. <br>
<br>
That one's easy, so we've proved ALL the PoP flagging mobs have the qualities of a rotation mob, including the ones that you can quest past. So why, as someone who feels that the mobs you can quest past should be an exception to this, why do I offer this proof that even the quest-past mobs are rotation worthy, and in fact, rotation by all but name?<br>
<br>
Because I want people to be sure to understand that any mob you *can't* quest past, should not be teamed on. <br>
<br>
I am asking, not telling. I ask that an exception be made to skip a time sink. I also recognize the validity of saying &quot;no&quot; to that exception, and recognize the validity of a rule that says, flat out &quot;No teaming on flag mobs as well as rotation mobs&quot;. Anyone who doesn't, is being a part of the problem. <br>
<br>
It is in this case, that saying 'but the mob isn't on a rotation' is splitting hairs. The mob <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>may as well be on a rotation</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and because the situation is so unique, it isn't. <br>
<br>
How many AoW's do you think BotS would have killed if he'd dropped 72 loot pieces the first time they killed him? Each time after?<br>
<br>
The point is the same; because there are such high numbers of valuable pieces from these mobs, the only reason they are not on an official rotation is for logistical reasons. <br>
<br>
Let me spell out the absolute nature of my position thusly:<br>
<br>
To those guilds currently killing PoP flagging mobs beyond the three that can be quested past; I believe they should be on rotation, or that convention should treat them as if they are on a rotation, without one being written down. <br>
<br>
Plain and simple, no matter what the outcome of this discussion about mobs that can be quested past, even if every single member of that rotation is on autopass, the flags those mobs drop are so desireable as to be teamed up on if they are not given major distinction. And that, in those circumstances, is the loot they'd otherwise be dropping, and warrents the rule that they must be killed in the same way as any other rotation mob. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><br>
The only unique situation here, is with three very specific mobs, that can be quested past. <br>
</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
All others that cannot be quested past, are no differant than the Avatar of War, or Tunare, or Lord Seru, or any other high end content of a zone or expansion. <br>
<br>
I suggest that the outcome of this discussion, and following rules, should be based off of people's reactions to this idea; if the majority, or hell, even a minority of people chime in that &quot;no, they want to team on all flagging mobs&quot; than I would like to add my voice to the discussion, again. If the decision is between teaming on all, or teaming on none, than I support teaming on *none*. A compromise is only valid if there is movement on both sides. An absolute view of teaming in either direction, to me, is wrong, but I'd rather be wrong and fair to those who have gone before, than be *just* wrong and fair to no one. <br>
<br>
There is a huge differance between being fair, and being greedy, and I really don't think that greedy should ever win. If the pressure to allow teaming all the way up was bowed to, than the greedy would win. <br>
<br>
Support getting to content without being forced to quest to it? <br>
Sure do.<br>
<br>
Support getting to content that you couldn't get to, any other way, without the detriments of being a formal alliance? Sure don't. <br>
<br>
So yeah, that's me. <br>
<br>
Either <br>
A. NO teaming at all<br>
or <br>
B. Teaming *ONLY* on mobs that can be quested past. <br>
<br>
Anything else is an abuse of the RTA; even this that we ask is an exception to the rules of the RTA, and should be remembered as an exception that is one made *willingly*. <br>
<br>
I'd remind anyone being obnoxious and rude, that not only are you in the general forum, but you are asking for a change, not telling people what to do. Even I know that. <br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
