<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Doomshade and Rumblecrush are good examples. They are OBVIOUSLY contested content. The smaller to mid range guilds race like a mofo to get to them first because of the decent loot they drop. I can't tell you how many times I have seen 2 or 3 guilds group up to take doomshade down. Were they a formal alliance? No.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ah, beautiful, not since college have I seen such obvious breaking of logical fallacies.  Who teamed on Doomshade?  Who teamed on Rumblecrush?  How do they exactly race to kill him the minute he spawns, but yet have these non-formal alliances winning the race?  Every time I have seen either of these die, it has been a race, between two guilds, and being that me and mine run to VT on a fairly regular basis, used to kill him ourselves, and have never seen what you describe, I’m going to need guilds named and more credible witnesses than someone who claims “well, I saw it with my own eyes, many times”.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> There is nothing wrong with teaming on mobs. Nothing wrong with teaming on Sontalak, and nothing wrong with teaming on AD.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes there is, but since you are in the segment that meets the criteria “can’t kill it on our own”, you choose not to see it that way.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> We ARE NOT talking about guilds getting more loot, or more shares on rotations than they should. GET THAT THROUGH YOUR HEADS.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes we are, and if you’d like, you can join the conversation.  Wanna team?  Fine, be an alliance for all your rotations and PoP encounters, or for none.  Selective teaming is bad, that is why it’s against the rules for rotations.  Most people understand the logic behind it.  If you don’t, get someone else to explain it to you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> He was the only person who has even come close to THIS ISSUE. The rest of you are flying off on tangents and freaking out about things that SHOULD not even be a concern at this point.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, Mil is just trying to come to a compromise.  Please note he has the same concerns many of us do – that these same guilds will use this precedent in the future to selectively team past rotation mobs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Lots of people have teamed on Sont, Vindi, and other raid level mobs with semi-contested content<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Who?  What guilds?  When?  I have never seen nor heard of any guild capable of killing Sontalak teaming him.  Same with Vindi, who I can’t believe you qualify as “semi-contested”.  He dies within an hour of spawning.  The ONLY reason Vindi isn’t on rotation is that the rotation system measures kills in days, and Vindi kills would have to be measured with times of day.  No one teams Vindi or Sont because they functionally have one loot.  An ad hoc alliance is not going to put forth the effort required to kill Vindi at the risk of no benefit whatsoever.  An ad hoc alliance wouldn’t continually kill Vindi, because once they did it on a regular basis. . .they are no longer ad hoc are they?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> The issue still remains that AD, Grummus, and Behemoth are then only mobs that we are talking about. They are not rotation mobs, and as has happened with mobs throughout the expansions, guilds will help each other kill mobs that are too hard for them, as long as they are not rotation mobs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, guilds have not helped each other through the various mobs throughout the various expansions, as the vast majority of desireable mobs have been on rotation.  The closest your claim comes to truth is Nagafen or the occasional Vox raid.  The reason for this?  No guild remains at L 52 to chain farm Nagafen and Vox when single group mobs drop better loot at L 60-65.  Nagafen was most heavily teamed by random pickup raids, because he was the only way to get to Ragefire.  Now that Ragefire has moved, you don’t see many Nagafen raids these days.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> See, Roggulbuk understand the issue.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Jeshter, I think you seriously need to reread Rogg’s post.  One key point he disagrees with you on is that selective teaming is bad and breaks the spirit of the rotation system.<br>
<br>
Since you have trouble finding the portions I will point them out for you:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> There are times when even mobs that are not on rotation, should not be teamed against, ever.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> The zones beyond drop loot that is 'guarded' by the flagging encounter. Teaming on mobs that cannot be quested past, to me, is like teaming up to kill a rotation mob;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> It is in this case, that saying 'but the mob isn't on a rotation' is splitting hairs. The mob may as well be on a rotation and because the situation is so unique, it isn't.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
and finally:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Either <br>
A. NO teaming at all<br>
or <br>
B. Teaming *ONLY* on mobs that can be quested past.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Consistency of argument Jeshter.  Make sure those who you want to say “understands it”, don’t contradict your own claim/argument.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Rogg,<br>
<br>
Good post, as always.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sprigg,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> On the very day that two guilds express a sincere interest in putting AD on rotation, I will consider this mob contested.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A mob doesn’t have to be on rotation to be contested, ask Jeshter.<br>
